						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Kulaśēkhara, 13+2nd year = A.D. 1205.</p>						

						<p>Portions completely worn out. Tiruvālavāyuḍaiyāṉ Chōḻagaṅgaṉ Aḻagiyapperumāḷ of Iḍattuvaḷi seems to have assigned some land as <hi rend="italic">jenmam</hi> to somebody (name lost) with the stipulation to measure out paddy at the rate of 6 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> per <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> to the temple of Aḻagiya-Āḻvār at Iḍattuvaḷi in Cheṅgāṭtirukkai a part of Veṇbuḷa-nāḍu, in Madurōdaya-vaḷanāḍu in Pāṇḍi-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Virudhunagar District Inscriptions</hi>, No. 137/2005, lines 1—6.]</p>						

						</summary>
